Class DatasetIdentifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.manager.DatasetIdentifier
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TransformedDatasetIdentifier

    public class DatasetIdentifier
extends Object
    Provides identification for the data regarding a specific attribute available from a data source.

      • DatasetIdentifier

        public DatasetIdentifier(DataSource source,
                         String dataset,
                         String colValueName,
                         String nameOperation,
                         boolean transformed)
        Constructor
        Parameters:
        source - The data source (directory, JDBC connection, or REST API) that provides access to the attribute data.
        dataset - The name of the dataset (file, table) that contains the attribute data.
        colValueName - The column name containing the attribute data to be used.
        nameOperation - The name of the operation supported on this attribute.
        transformed - Boolean indicating whether this data need be transformed.

      • generateUUID

        private UUID generateUUID(String nameOperation,
                          boolean transformed)
        Generates a (non-random) Universally Unique Dataset Identifier (UUID).
        Parameters:
        nameOperation - The name of the operation supported on this attribute.
        transformed - Boolean indicating whether this data need be transformed.
        Returns:
        A 128-bit value that represents the UUID.

        public void setOperation(int operation)
        Assign the type of the search operation to the identifier.
        Parameters:

      • setDataSource

      • setQueryable

        public void setQueryable(boolean queryable)
        Specify that this attribute data will be involved or not in similarity search requests.
        Parameters:
        queryable - Boolean value: True, if this attribute may be specified in similarity search queries; False indicates that this dataset is used solely as a lookup.

        Parameters:
        prefixURL - The prefix to be appended to the entity identifiers (coming from values in attrKey).
